<br>
that is what I'm worried about.. It will make things too easy, and when something has either no challenge (too easy) or no way to overcome something (cough, deathtouch), it becomes very boring and will disinterest most people.<br>
<br>
Like I said, why not just give everyone god mode, or make people respawn like in Unreal, Quake or some other 3D shooter <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
p.s. I never said rogues didn't have useful skills, their skills kickass. What I meant is, rogues' abilities, strengths, and skills do not allow them to do a lot of stuff, like soloing well, without very rare, very hard to attain gear, which takes more time then asking a local mage. Like I said, if something like this could be put into beneficial-for-melee-classes terms, it would be like magicians getting Summon: Primal weapon.<br>
<br>
Also, its an odd shift. One moment Focus items were something dreamed of, and idealized to be placed on higher-end encounters and monsters. Then, few hours and one big patch later, suddenly EVERYONE is able to get them without effort or risk. does.not.make.sense.!<br>
<br>
These focus items aren't only an increase of damage, but of overall efficiency. Reduced agro to mobs--allows the caster to nuke more without getting a quad 1154 from meanie AOW or such. Reduced spell casting times--allows those same casters to nuke, cast, heal, buff, debuff, mez, root, dot, summon, whatever faster, allowing for more efficiency and damage dealt in a period of time. Reduced Casting COST-- Cheal chains lasting longer, wizzies burning longer, and getting those extra few nukes/heals in. Not enough? Increased damage--so now, while those casters are doing damage FASTER, with less agro and costing less mana, they do MORE DAMAGE!<br>
<br>
I really dont mean to pick on wizzies, but here's another example.<br>
<br>
Dragonbane:<br>
normally, cost 450 mana, deals 2000 damage, and takes 6.0 seconds to cast.<br>
WITHOUT innate crit and crit AAXP points put in, and WITHOUT magician focus items, a wizard effectively does 2000 damage for 450 mana (roughly 4.44 damage per mana) in six seconds.<br>
<br>
now, WITH the summoned focus items, we need to shave 15% off the mana cost, casting time, and add 15% to damage. That comes out to: 2300 damage for 382 mana (6.02 damage per mana), in 5.1 seconds.<br>
<br>
Thats an increase of 1.58 extra damage per mana point, which is over 13% overall increase of efficiency--NOT damage, if you want damage approx, go parse-- (of course, results vary depending on spells used), and NONE of this is accounting for critical blasts, at all.<br>
<br>
An increase in effectiveness that large should warrant some risk to attaining it. That's all I'm saying. If these items were dropping off *insert mob here in luclin who is dropping 923846234 bst weapons which noone wants* instead of that crap, it would be great. Creates more desirable raid targets (ala, high end EQ content, the stuff that people and guilds fight over hourly in this game), and allows the players to become more powerful, instead of pretty much handing it to them. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14427">Lauralan of the Nexus</a>, 60th Warlock<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21609">Tyros Darkheart</a>, 60th Warlord<br>Lorean Korath, 53rd Vicar.<br><Mortalis> Antonius Bayle</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulauralankanan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lauralan Kanan</A> at: 3/20/02 5:42:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ualdarionshard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aldarion Shard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/02 6:12:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22859.topic&index=64>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> argument</span><hr size=1> this argument is getting buried down in details.<br>
