you mention a good point... yes rogues geta  huge damage upgrade via enchanter haste spells and mob-dropped items such as FBSS and 15/20 daggers... and then ask, but wouldnt it be unbalancing if those were summoned for free?<br>
<br>
yes.<br>
<br>
theyre not.  the 100% increase only comes from a COMBINATION (via interclass balance) of:<br>
1.  buffs cast by ENC,SHM, BRD<br>
...for about 60-70% haste<br>
and<br>
2. items dropped from mobs.<br>
....for another, say, 40%.<br>
<br>
together, they make up about 100 as a nice average number.<br>
<br>
now the situation that focus items will create for casters is this:<br>
<br>
summoned items summoned by mages, <br>
.....for about 10-15% increase<br>
and<br>
maybe someday soon...<br>
<br>
mob dropped items for about 20-30% increases...<br>
<br>
and end up with maybe 50% as a &quot;focus cap&quot;, as melees have a ca. 105-120ish haste cap at 60 with bard song etc...<br>
<br>
